title: Add TTS support via mimic3
body:
If the new "mimic_endpoint" configuration option is set, the bot will do a few basic TTS jokes.

"mimic_endpoint" needs to be to the base URL of the mimic API and include the trailing slash (e.g. "http://localhost:8675/api/")

body:

Release notes

Sourced from reqwest's releases.

v0.11.14

What's Changed

  • Adds Proxy::no_proxy(url) that works like the NO_PROXY environment variable.
  • Adds multipart::Part::headers(headers) method to add custom headers.
  • (wasm) Add Response::bytes_stream().
  • Perf: several internal optimizations reducing copies and memory allocations.
